The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 India to tour SA at year-end 

 - U-19 side to play in Pakistan in September 

Mumbai: The Board of Control for Cricket in India (BCCI) announced on Wednesday it had finalised a Test and one-day tour of South Africa for November and December this year. 

The tour comprises five one-dayers, three Tests and a four-day practice match, BCCI secretary Niranjan Shah said on Wednesday. The dates will be confirmed later. 

Shah said India had also confirmed participation in a tri-series with Sri Lanka and South Africa in Sri Lanka in August and September. 

Shah and former president Inderjit Singh Bindra leave for the United States on Thursday for talks with the American Cricket Association and the West Indies Cricket Board on a programme of three or five one-day matches between India and the West Indies in North America in August and September. 

We are to discuss when and where to play those matches, Shah said. 

Meanwhile, the India under-19 side would visit Pakistan this September to play three one-dayers and two four-day matches against the hosts. 

BCCIs Tours Programmes and Fixtures Committee also finalised India A teams tour of South Africa in March-April next year. 

India A would play three Tests and four one-dayers against their South African counterparts. South Africa A has been in vited to play in Duleep Trophy as the overseas squad for the forthcoming season. It will also play five one-day matches against India A. 

